        content: "app_id: code\nskill_id: get_docs\nresults[1]{library_id,library_title,library_description,documentation,word_count,source,error}:\n  /sveltejs/svelte,Svelte,\"Svelte is a compiler that transforms declarative UI components into efficient JavaScript that surgically updates the DOM, offering a new approach to building web applications.\",\"### Declare a reactive state variable using $state rune in Svelte\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/02-runes/01-what-are-runes.md\\n\\nThis snippet demonstrates how to declare a reactive state variable in Svelte using the `$state` rune. The `$state` rune is a Svelte keyword that signals to the compiler that the `message` variable should be reactive, meaning changes to its value will automatically trigger updates in the UI. It behaves like a function call but is a built-in language construct.\\n\\n```js\\nlet message = $state('hello');\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Compute reactive state using $derived in Svelte\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/07-misc/01-best-practices.md\\n\\nDemonstrates the preferred method for computing values from state using the $derived rune instead of manually updating variables within an $effect. This ensures cleaner code and better performance.\\n\\n```javascript\\nlet num = 0;\\n// do this\\nlet square = $derived(num * num);\\n\\n// don't do this\\nlet square;\\n\\n$effect(() => {\\n\\tsquare = num * num;\\n});\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Create computed values using $derived in Svelte 5\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/07-misc/07-v5-migration-guide.md\\n\\nReplaces the '$:' syntax for derivations. The $derived rune ensures values are always current, determines dependencies at runtime, and is fully compatible with TypeScript.\\n\\n```svelte\\n<script>\\n\\tlet count = $state(0);\\n\\tconst double = $derived(count * 2);\\n</script>\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### $derived - Basic Derived State\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/02-runes/03-$derived.md\\n\\nDeclares derived state that automatically updates when its dependencies change. The expression inside $derived should be free of side-effects and cannot contain state mutations.\\n\\n```APIDOC\\n## $derived\\n\\n### Description\\nCreates reactive derived state that automatically recalculates when its dependencies change. The expression must be side-effect free and cannot contain state mutations.\\n\\n### Syntax\\n```svelte\\nlet derived_value = $derived(expression);\\n```\\n\\n### Parameters\\n- **expression** (any) - Required - A side-effect free expression that computes the derived value. Any state read synchronously is tracked as a dependency.\\n\\n### Usage Example\\n```svelte\\n<script>\\n\\tlet count = $state(0);\\n\\tlet doubled = $derived(count * 2);\\n</script>\\n\\n<button onclick={() => count++}>\\n\\t{doubled}\\n</button>\\n\\n<p>{count} doubled is {doubled}</p>\\n```\\n\\n### Behavior\\n- Derived values are recalculated when dependencies change\\n- Code in Svelte components executes only once at creation\\n- Without $derived, values would maintain their original value even when dependencies change\\n- Can be used to mark class fields as derived\\n- Prior to Svelte 5.25, deriveds were read-only; now they can be temporarily reassigned\\n```\\n\\n--------------------------------\\n\\n### Declare derived state with $derived\\n\\nSource: https://github.com/sveltejs/svelte/blob/main/documentation/docs/02-runes/03-$derived.md\\n\\nUse $derived to create a reactive value that automatically updates when its dependencies change. The expression should be side-effect free.\\n\\n```svelte\\n<script>\\n\\tlet count = $state(0);\\n\\tlet doubled = $derived(count * 2);\\n</script>\\n\\n<button onclick={() => count++}>\\n\\t{doubled}\\n</button>\\n\\n<p>{count} doubled is {doubled}</p>\\n```\",429,context7,null\nresult_count: 1\nstatus: finished\nembed_ref: get_docs-iG1\nembed_id: bf346f38-6f8f-4a29-b7b4-00eacda289e5\nlibrary: Svelte 5\nquestion: How to use $state and $derived runes?",
